#. type: Content of: <guide><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "A short guide to Gentoo/FreeBSD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><abstract>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:37
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This document gives some general information on FreeBSD, as well as\n"
"installation instructions for Gentoo/FreeBSD. It also includes some reference\n"
"for people interested in helping out with development.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction to FreeBSD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is FreeBSD?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:56
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Be sure to read the Gentoo/FreeBSD <uri\n"
"link=\"http://wiki.gentoo.org/wiki/Gentoo_FreeBSD\">wiki page</uri> for up-to-date\n"
"installation instructions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:62
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<uri link=\"http://www.freebsd.org/\">FreeBSD</uri> is a free (<uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.freebsd.org/copyright/freebsd-license.html\">license</uri>)\n"
"Unix-like operating system. Back in 1993 when development of <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.386bsd.org/\">386BSD</uri> stopped, two projects were born:\n"
"<uri link=\"http://www.netbsd.org/\">NetBSD</uri>, commonly known to run on a\n"
"huge number of architectures, and FreeBSD which supports the x86, amd64, ia64,\n"
"sparc64 and alpha platforms. FreeBSD is renowned for its stability, performance\n"
"and security, thus being used from small to huge companies all over the world.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:73
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"FreeBSD's current production release is version 7.1. Gentoo/FreeBSD is based on\n"
"version 6.2 and older versions of Gentoo/FreeBSD are discontinued and no\n"
"longer supported.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is Gentoo/FreeBSD?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:88
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<uri link=\"/proj/en/gentoo-alt/bsd/fbsd/\">Gentoo/FreeBSD</uri> is a subproject\n"
"of the <uri link=\"/proj/en/gentoo-alt/\">Gentoo/Alt project</uri>,  with the\n"
"goal of providing a fully-capable FreeBSD operating system featuring design\n"
"sensibilities taken from Gentoo Linux, such as the init system and the Portage\n"
"package management system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "FreeBSD and Linux"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:102
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Users migrating from Linux to FreeBSD commonly consider the two operating\n"
"systems \"almost the same\". In fact, FreeBSD really shares a lot of similarities\n"
"with Linux distributions in general. Nevertheless, it has some key differences\n"
"that are worth noting:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:110
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Contrary to Linux, which actually only refers to the kernel, FreeBSD is a\n"
"    complete operating system, consisting of a C library, userland tools and\n"
"    much more. This development approach makes the overall system very\n"
"    consistent.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:116
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Contrary to the Linux kernel, FreeBSD development is not led by one person,\n"
"    but instead managed by a small group of people called the <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://www.freebsd.org/doc/en_US.ISO8859-1/articles/contributors/staff-committers.html\">Core\n"
"    Team</uri>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Besides, FreeBSD also has some technical differences which set it apart\n"
"from Linux. Some of them are very important to know, even if you don't plan on\n"
"joining the Gentoo/FreeBSD development effort:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:131
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    To get run-time dynamic linking functions like <c>dlopen()</c>, programs do\n"
"    not need to be linked against libdl like on GNU/Linux. Instead they are\n"
"    linked against libc.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:136
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    FreeBSD doesn't have an official tool for kernel compilation, thus you'll\n"
"    have to resolve feature dependencies on your own.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:140
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    FreeBSD uses UFS/UFS-2 as its filesystems and has no official support for\n"
"    e.g. ReiserFS or XFS. However, there are projects for adding read-only\n"
"    support for these filesystems. Accessing ext2/ext3 partitions is already\n"
"    possible, but you cannot install your system on them.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:152
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing Gentoo/FreeBSD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:154
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting the CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:158
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After this short introduction, it's about time to finally install\n"
"Gentoo/FreeBSD. Unfortunately, we currently lack our own installation media, so\n"
"you have to choose between two alternative installation methods. The first\n"
"would be to use an existing FreeBSD installation to partition your hard drive\n"
"and use it as a base for installing Gentoo/FreeBSD. This guide will describe how\n"
"to use the <uri link=\"http://www.freesbie.org/\">FreeSBIE LiveCD</uri> as\n"
"an installation medium for Gentoo/FreeBSD.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:168
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are intending to use FreeSBIE for installing Gentoo/FreeBSD, please make\n"
"sure to use a version based on FreeBSD 6.x, such as FreeSBIE 2.0 (or one of its\n"
"release candidates). You can download it from <uri\n"
"link=\"http://torrent.freesbie.org/\">FreeSBIE's Bittorrent tracker</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:175
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, boot the CD in order to begin the installation process. You'll be\n"
"presented with a login screen.  The username is <c>freesbie</c>, and there is\n"
"no password.  Next, run <c>sudo su</c> to become root, and optionally setup a\n"
"password. If you want to pass time during the installation process, you can run\n"
"<c>startx</c> to enter into an Xfce environment, suitable for web browsing,\n"
"AIM, and other things. Unlike Linux, FreeBSD bases the name of your interface\n"
"on the driver for the interface. For example, the Intel EtherExpress driver\n"
"(fxp) appears as fxp0 (driver fxp, first network card). To see what your\n"
"interface is, use <c>ifconfig</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:186
#, no-wrap
msgid "Finding out the network interface name using ifconfig"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:187
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>ifconfig</i>\n"
"fxp0: flags=8843&lt;UP,BROADCAST,RUNNING,SIMPLEX,MULTICAST&gt; mtu 1500\n"
"        options=8&lt;VLAN_MTU&gt;\n"
"        inet6 fe80::2d0::b7ff:febc:4fe3%fxp0 prefixlen 64 scopeid 0x1\n"
"        inet 192.168.0.106 netmask 0xffffff00 broadcast 192.168.0.255\n"
"        ether 00:d0:b7:bc:4f:e3\n"
"        media: Ethernet autoselect (100baseTX &lt;full-duplex&gt;)\n"
"        status: active\n"
"lo0: flags=8007&lt;LOOPBACK,MULTICAST&gt; mtu 16384\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:199
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If the original DHCP request during the CD bootup failed, you can use the\n"
"<c>dhclient</c> command to obtain an IP:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:203
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining a DHCP address using dhclient"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:204
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>dhclient fxp0</i>\n"
"DHCPDISCOVER on fxp0 to 255.255.255.255 port 67 interval 9\n"
"DHCPOFFER from 192.168.0.1\n"
"DHCPREQUEST on fxp0 to 255.255.255.255 port 67\n"
"DHCPACK from 192.168.0.1\n"
"bound to 192.168.0.106 -- renewal in 302400 seconds\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "The output presented here will differ based on your network.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:219
#, no-wrap
msgid "Partitioning the Drive"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:223
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that we have a mount point, it's time to partition the drive. This is done\n"
"with the <c>sysinstall</c> command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:227
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running the sysinstall command to fdisk the drive"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:228
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>sysinstall diskPartitionEditor diskPartitionWrite</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:232
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We recommend that you use the default layout. Press enter at the dialog, then\n"
"press <b>a</b> followed by <b>q</b> to accept the default layout. The next\n"
"screen will present you with the option of a bootloader. For this option,\n"
"choose \"None\" as we'll be installing the bootloader later on. Next comes the\n"
"actual partition sizing and mount points.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:240
#, no-wrap
msgid "This next step also uses <c>sysinstall</c>, but with different arguments:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running sysinstall to setup partition sizing and mount points"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:244
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>sysinstall diskLabelEditor diskLabelCommit</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:248
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Here, we'll refrain from using the automatic layout, and create one giant root\n"
"partition, followed by a swap partition. Hit <b>c</b> to create a new\n"
"partition. A dialog prompts you to enter a size. Go ahead and do so, using\n"
"MB/GB for setting different sizes, or C for cylinders. For root, choose FS as\n"
"the partition type, and set the mount point as <path>/mnt/</path>. <e>If\n"
"you do not adjust the mount point, it will overwrite the FreeSBIE\n"
"environment!</e> As <path>/boot</path> is not a separate partition, you'll\n"
"need to disable soft-updates, or your system will not boot! To do so, use the\n"
"arrow keys to navigate to your newly created partition, then hit the <b>s</b>\n"
"key, until \"Newfs\" contains no <b>+S</b>. Now navigate the arrow keys until\n"
"the \"Disk\" line is highlighted, and hit <b>c</b> again to create a swap\n"
"partition.  Generally, we recommend a swap space that is twice the size of your\n"
"RAM. Choose SWAP as the partition type, and don't worry about soft-updates, as\n"
"it does not apply to swap. Now we're finished, so hit <b>q</b> to finish the\n"
"process.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:266
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When choosing a different mountpoint than <path>/</path> for your partition,\n"
"<c>sysinstall</c> will actually create a 'd' slice, which the bootloader won't\n"
"boot from. To fix this, run the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:272
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Please, make sure ad0s1 is unmounted before running the following command, \n"
"otherwise it will not work.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:276
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fixing the root partition letter"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:277
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>disklabel ad0s1 | sed 's/^  d:/  a:/' | disklabel -R ad0s1 /dev/stdin</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:281
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This will finalize the partitioning process, and format the drive in UFS for\n"
"FreeBSD to utilize. This will also mount the drive for you at the mount point\n"
"specified earlier (<path>/mnt/</path>). You can verify this worked by\n"
"running <c>mount</c>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:287
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verifying the new disk layout was mounted with mount"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:288
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>mount</i>\n"
"...\n"
"/dev/ad0s1a on /mnt (ufs, local)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:294
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that you have mounted the target partition, it is time to start on the\n"
"Gentoo setup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:301
#, no-wrap
msgid "Gentoo Setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:305
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, we need to download a stage3 tarball and unpack it into the chroot.\n"
"Point your browser to\n"
"<uri>http://distfiles.gentoo.org/experimental/x86/freebsd/stages/</uri>, grab the\n"
"latest snapshot, and unpack it into the mountpoint:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:311
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining and unpacking a stage3 tarball"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:312
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>cd /mnt/</i>\n"
"<comment>(Any other Gentoo mirror which includes the experimental/ directory will also work.)</comment>\n"
"# <i>wget http://distfiles.gentoo.org/experimental/x86/freebsd/stages/stage3-x86-freebsd-6.2-r1.tar.bz2</i>\n"
"# <i>tar -jxvpf stage3-x86-freebsd-6.2-r1.tar.bz2</i>\n"
"<comment>(You can delete the tarball with the following command if you want to.)</comment>\n"
"# <i>rm stage3-x86-freebsd-6.2-r1.tar.bz2</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:321
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want you can use the transition overlay that contains semi-experimental\n"
"ebuilds with patches not yet in the main Portage tree, but does allow a wider\n"
"range of supported packages, please refer to the <uri\n"
"link=\"/proj/en/gentoo-alt/contribute/index.xml?part=1&amp;chap=3\">Gentoo/ALT\n"
"overlay documentation</uri>.  Please note that the overlay is not critical and\n"
"you can easily install and use Gentoo/FreeBSD without it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:330
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In order for your install to work, you need to mount the <path>/dev</path>\n"
"filesystem from the currently running system into the Gentoo/FreeBSD mount\n"
"point before proceeding with the chroot.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:335
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mounting the /dev filesystem and chrooting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:336
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>mount -t devfs none /mnt/dev/</i>\n"
"# <i>cp /etc/resolv.conf /mnt/etc/</i>\n"
"# <i>chroot /mnt/ /bin/bash</i>\n"
"# <i>env-update &amp;&amp; source /etc/profile</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:343
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After you obtain the Gentoo/FreeBSD overlay, it's time to link\n"
"<path>/etc/portage/make.profile</path> to the correct profile and get your\n"
"<path>/etc/portage/make.conf</path> ready for Gentoo/FreeBSD.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:349
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now, you have to obtain a copy of the main Gentoo Portage tree, which depending\n"
"on your connection might take quite a while.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:353
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining the Portage tree"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:354
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge --sync</i>\n"
"<comment>(It's also possible to retrieve the Portage tree in another way:)</comment>\n"
"# <i>cd /</i>\n"
"# <i>wget http://distfiles.gentoo.org/snapshots/portage-latest.tar.bz2</i>\n"
"# <i>tar -xjf portage-latest.tar.bz2 -C /usr/</i>\n"
"# <i>emerge --metadata</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:362
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up the profile and editing /etc/portage/make.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:363
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>ln -sf /usr/portage/profiles/default-bsd/fbsd/6.2/x86/ /etc/portage/make.profile</i>\n"
"# <i>nano /etc/portage/make.conf</i>\n"
"<comment>(Please make sure you add at least the following entries:)</comment>\n"
"CHOST=\"i686-gentoo-freebsd6.2\"\n"
"FEATURES=\"collision-protect\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:371
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <c>~x86-fbsd</c> keyword does not yet fully cover the same tree as\n"
"<c>~x86</c>, but please <e>do not</e> put <c>~x86</c> in ACCEPT_KEYWORDS. Rather\n"
"use <path>/etc/portage/package.accept_keywords</path> to test packages, and\n"
"report working packages on <uri\n"
"link=\"http://bugs.gentoo.org/enter_bug.cgi?product=Gentoo%2FAlt\">Bugzilla</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:379
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you want, you can now rebuild the system's core packages.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:382
#, no-wrap
msgid "Rebuilding the FreeBSD core packages (optional)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:383
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge -e system</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:390
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up for Booting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:392
#, no-wrap
msgid "Set your time zone"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:396
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First make sure your date and time is set correctly using <c>date\n"
"yyyymmddHHMM</c>. Use UTC time.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:400
#, no-wrap
msgid "Set the date and UTC time"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:401
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Check the clock)</comment>\n"
"# <i>date</i>\n"
"Mon Mar  6 00:14:13 UTC 2006\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Set the current date and time if required)</comment>\n"
"# <i>date 200603060016</i> <comment>(Format is yyyymmddHHMM)</comment>\n"
"Mon Mar  6 00:16:00 UTC 2006\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:411
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next, set your time zone information by using the correct listing in\n"
"<path>/usr/share/zoneinfo</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:415
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting your timezone"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:416
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>ls /usr/share/zoneinfo</i>\n"
"<comment>(Using Brussels as an example)</comment>\n"
"# <i>cp /usr/share/zoneinfo/Europe/Brussels /etc/localtime</i>\n"
"\n"
"# <i>date</i>\n"
"Wed Mar  8 00:46:05 CET 2006\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:425
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Edit <path>/etc/timezone</path> to define the time zone you used\n"
"previously.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:429
#, no-wrap
msgid "Edit /etc/timezone"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:430
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>nano -w /etc/timezone</i>\n"
"Europe/Brussels\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:437
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kernel Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:441
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you ran <c>emerge -e system</c>, the sources for the FreeBSD kernel were\n"
"installed to <path>/usr/src/sys</path>. If you skipped this step, you can get\n"
"them in the following way:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:446
#, no-wrap
msgid "Getting the FreeBSD kernel sources"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:447
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>emerge freebsd-sources</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:451
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Configuring and compiling a custom kernel is quite different from compiling\n"
"Linux, so if you are not familiar with the process we encourage you to have a\n"
"look at <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.freebsd.org/doc/en_US.ISO8859-1/books/handbook/kernelconfig.html\">\n"
"chapter 8</uri> of the FreeBSD handbook. For now, you can do an installation of\n"
"the GENERIC kernel, which works on most systems. To begin, enter the source\n"
"directory for the kernel:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:461
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Please note that currently only the \"Traditional\" way of building the kernel is\n"
"supported on Gentoo/FreeBSD!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:465
#, no-wrap
msgid "Entering the kernel source directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:466
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>cd /usr/src/sys/</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:470
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Looking over the layout, you'll see various architectures and subdirectories\n"
"for various parts of the kernel. To begin the installation, we head into the\n"
"<path>i386/conf/</path> directory:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:475
#, no-wrap
msgid "The kernel configuration directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:476
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>cd i386/conf/</i>\n"
"# <i>ls</i>\n"
".cvsignore      GENERIC         Makefile        PAE\n"
"DEFAULTS        GENERIC.hints   NOTES           SMP\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:483
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The main files to note are <path>GENERIC</path> and <path>GENERIC.hints</path>.\n"
"As it will be needed by the installation of the kernel, go ahead and copy\n"
"<path>GENERIC.hints</path> file to <path>/boot/device.hints</path>:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:488
#, no-wrap
msgid "Copying over the GENERIC.hints file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:489
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>cp GENERIC.hints /boot/device.hints</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:493
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This file is used by the kernel drivers for basic configuration information\n"
"such as IRQ settings. Now it's time to configure the kernel. FreeBSD uses the\n"
"<c>config</c> command to do this. <c>config</c> uses the given file (in this\n"
"instance GENERIC) to copy over the required build files to a\n"
"<path>compile</path> directory in the parent directory. <path>GENERIC</path> is\n"
"similiar to the <path>.config</path> file for the Linux kernel. Run\n"
"<c>config</c> to produce the build directory:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:502
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring the kernel build"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:503
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>config GENERIC</i>\n"
"Kernel build directory is ../compile/GENERIC\n"
"Don't forget to ''make cleandepend; make depend''\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:509
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>config</c> has created a GENERIC build directory for us in the parent\n"
"directory. <c>cd</c> into it, then run the following to do a complete build:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:513
#, no-wrap
msgid "Building and installing the kernel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:514
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>cd ../compile/GENERIC</i>\n"
"# <i>make cleandepend &amp;&amp; make depend &amp;&amp; make &amp;&amp; make install</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:519
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This will give us a complete kernel to work with.  Now we'll need to setup the\n"
"bootloader for the kernel to boot. The next chapter will discuss two methods of\n"
"setting up the bootloader: <c>boot0</c> and <c>grub</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:527
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up the bootloader (boot0)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:531
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>boot0</c> is the FreeBSD bootloader. Previously, it was the only supported\n"
"bootloader until <c>grub</c> was introduced into ports with UFS slice support.\n"
"To install and configure <c>boot0</c>, run the following. Remember to replace\n"
"<c>adXsY</c> with the actual number and slice of your disk.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:537
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing and setting up boot0"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:538
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge boot0</i>\n"
"<comment>(Leave the chroot environment)</comment>\n"
"# <i>exit</i>\n"
"<comment>(Issued from outside the chroot)</comment>\n"
"# <i>fdisk -B -b /mnt/boot/boot0 /dev/adX</i>\n"
"# <i>chroot /mnt/ /bin/bash</i>\n"
"# <i>disklabel -B adXsY</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:548
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you need additional information on setting up <c>boot0</c>, please consult\n"
"<uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.freebsd.org/doc/en_US.ISO8859-1/books/handbook/boot.html\">chapter\n"
"12</uri> of the FreeBSD handbook. Now it's time to do some basic system\n"
"configuration and settings.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:556
#, no-wrap
msgid "The next section will look at using the alternative bootloader, <c>grub</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:562
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up the bootloader (grub)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:566
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"As of grub 0.97-r1, UFS slices are readable to <c>grub</c>. This lets us use\n"
"<c>grub</c> as a bootloader, the prefered method for those coming from a Linux\n"
"background. To begin, emerge <c>grub</c> and setup the label as bootable.\n"
"Remember to replace <c>adXsY</c> with the actual number and slice of your disk.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:572
#, no-wrap
msgid "Emerge grub"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:573
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>emerge grub</i>\n"
"# <i>disklabel -B adXsY</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:578
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now run <c>grub</c> to bring up the command prompt, and set up the partition as\n"
"shown:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:582
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up grub"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:583
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(This is done to prevent disk error 29)</comment>\n"
"# <i>sysctl kern.geom.debugflags=16</i>\n"
"# <i>grub</i>\n"
"<comment>(Example using ad0s1d)</comment>\n"
"grub&gt; <i>root (hd0,0,d)</i>\n"
" Filesystem type is ufs2, partition type 0xa5\n"
"\n"
"grub&gt; <i>setup (hd0)</i>\n"
" Checking if \"/boot/grub/stage1\" exists... yes\n"
" Checking if \"/boot/grub/stage2\" exists... yes\n"
" Checking if \"/boot/grub/ufs2_stage1_5\" exists... yes\n"
" Running \"embed /boot/grub/ufs2_stage1_5 (hd0)\"... 14 sectors are embedded.\n"
"succeeded\n"
" Running \"install /boot/grub/stage1 (hd0) (hd0)1+14 p (hd0,0,d)/boot/grub/stage\n"
"2 /boot/grub/menu.lst\"... succeeded\n"
"Done.\n"
"\n"
"grub&gt; quit\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:604
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To make the loader find the kernel on a specific slice (the default is 'a'),\n"
"add a <c>vfs.root.mountfrom</c> line to the <path>/boot/loader.conf</path>\n"
"file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:609
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tell the loader where to look for the kernel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:610
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>echo 'vfs.root.mountfrom=\"ufs:ad0s1d\"' >> /boot/loader.conf</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:614
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"When you first boot, you may not receive a grub menu. If so, run this at the\n"
"prompt:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:618
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting the kernel with no menu"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:619
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"grub&gt; <i>find /boot/grub/stage1</i>\n"
"<comment>(The output here is what you'll use in the next command)</comment>\n"
" (hd0,0,d)\n"
"\n"
"grub&gt; <i>kernel (hd0,0,d)/boot/loader</i>\n"
"  [FreeBSD-a.out, loadaddr=0x200000, text=0x1000, data=0x3a000, bss=0x0, entry=0x200000]\n"
"\n"
"grub&gt; <i>boot</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:630
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For more information on configuring grub, please refer to the <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=1&amp;chap=10#doc_chap2\">Gentoo\n"
"Linux Handbook</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><warn>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:636
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Grub doesn't follow UFS symlinks so be sure to delete the\n"
"<path>/boot/grub/menu.lst</path> symlink and to use <path>menu.lst</path> to\n"
"setup Grub (<path>grub.conf</path> isn't used).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:644
#, no-wrap
msgid "System configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:648
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, we are going to setup the filesystem mounting points in\n"
"<path>/etc/fstab</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:652
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing the filesystem in /etc/fstab"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:653
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>nano /etc/fstab</i>\n"
"<comment>(This is an example, replace X and Y with the correct numbers for your hard disk.)</comment>\n"
"#Device         Mountpoint      Fstype          Options         Dump    Pass\n"
"/dev/adXsYb     none            swap            sw              0       0\n"
"/dev/adXsYa     /               ufs             rw              1       1\n"
"/dev/adXsYe     /usr/home       ufs             rw              2       2\n"
"/dev/adXsYd     /tmp            ufs             rw              2       2\n"
"/dev/acdX       /cdrom          cd9660          ro,noauto       0       0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:664
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now would also be a good time to set up your network connection before the final\n"
"reboot. You can find all the information necessary to configure your network in\n"
"the <uri link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=4&amp;chap=1\">Gentoo\n"
"Handbook</uri>. To have your network interface activated at boot time, you have\n"
"to add it to the default runlevel:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:671
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding your network adapter to the default runlevel"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:672
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>rc-update add net.fxp0 default</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:676
#, no-wrap
msgid "Your system's hostname can be changed in <path>/etc/conf.d/hostname</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:679
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting up the machine's hostname"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:680
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>nano /etc/conf.d/hostname</i>\n"
"<comment>(Set the HOSTNAME variable to your hostname)</comment>\n"
"HOSTNAME=\"tux\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:686
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You should also configure your domain name, which is done in the\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/domainname</path> file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:690
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting the domainname"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:691
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>nano /etc/conf.d/domainname</i>\n"
"<comment>(Set the dns_domain variable to your domain name, and lo to your local\n"
"network interface)</comment>\n"
"dns_domain_lo=\"homenetwork\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:698
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have a NIS domain, you need to define it in the\n"
"<path>/etc/conf.d/domainname</path> file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:702
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting the NIS domainname"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:703
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>nano /etc/conf.d/domainname</i>\n"
"<comment>(Set the nis_domain variable to your NIS domain name, and lo to your local network interface)</comment>\n"
"nis_domain_lo=\"my-nisdomain\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:709
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For more information on domainnames and networking, please refer to the <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=1&amp;chap=8#doc_chap2\">Gentoo\n"
"Linux Handbook</uri>, and please read the documentation in\n"
"<path>/usr/share/doc/openrc-*/net.example.bz2</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:716
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In case you need to use another keyboard layout for your language, you have to\n"
"set the correct value in <path>/etc/conf.d/syscons</path>. The following example\n"
"uses the Spanish layout, so you'll have to adjust it to your need if you want to\n"
"use another one.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:722
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing your keyboard layout (Optional)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:723
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>nano /etc/conf.d/syscons</i>\n"
"KEYMAP=\"spanish.iso.acc\"\n"
"<comment>(Possible layouts can be found in /usr/share/syscons/keymaps).</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:729
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now would be a good time to set a password for the <c>root</c> user and to add\n"
"another user account for your day-to-day work.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:733
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the root password and adding a new user"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:734
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>passwd</i>\n"
"# <i>adduser</i>\n"
"Username: <i>fred</i>\n"
"Full Name: <i>Fred Smith</i>\n"
"<comment>(Accepting the default here, just hit Enter.)</comment>\n"
"Uid (Leave empty for default):\n"
"<comment>(OK to accept the default here as well; hit Enter.)</comment>\n"
"Login group [fred]:\n"
"<comment>(Enter your groups here, space separated. They must exist.)</comment>\n"
"Login group is fred. Invite fred into other groups? []: wheel portage\n"
"<comment>(OK to accept the default here, hit Enter)</comment>\n"
"Login class [default]:\n"
"<comment>(Somewhat of a personal preference.  Make sure the shell exists in /etc/shells)</comment>\n"
"Shell (sh bash tcsh csh esh ksh zsh sash nologin) [sh] <i>bash</i>\n"
"<comment>(OK to accept the default here, hit Enter for all these)</comment>\n"
"User password-based authentication [yes]\n"
"Use an empty password (yes/no) [no]:\n"
"Use a random password? (yes/no) [no]:\n"
"Enter password: <i>password goes here</i>\n"
"Enter password again: <i>retype it</i>\n"
"<comment>(OK to accept the default here, hit Enter)</comment>\n"
"Lock out the account after creation? [no]:\n"
"Username    : fred\n"
"Password    : *****\n"
"Full Name   : Fred Smith\n"
"<comment>(This will vary)</comment>\n"
"Uid         : 1002\n"
"Class       :\n"
"Groups      : fred wheel portage\n"
"Home        : /home/fred\n"
"Shell       : /bin/bash\n"
"Locked      : no\n"
"<comment>(Confirm the information is correct)</comment>\n"
"OK? (yes/no): <i>yes</i>\n"
"adduser: INFO: Sucessfully added (fred) to the user database\n"
"Add another user? (yes/no): <i>no</i>\n"
"Goodbye!\n"
"#\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:775
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Congratulations, you have just finished your Gentoo/FreeBSD installation which\n"
"you can start exploring after the final reboot. Have fun!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:779
#, no-wrap
msgid "Rebooting the system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:780
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>exit</i>\n"
"# <i>reboot</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:789
#, no-wrap
msgid "Developing for Gentoo/FreeBSD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:791
#, no-wrap
msgid "How to help"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:795
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There are many things you could help with, depending on your skill level and\n"
"spare time:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:801
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Working on current ebuilds: this means working closely with ebuild\n"
"    maintainers in order to create patches or modify ebuilds in a way that can\n"
"    be accepted into the main tree.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:806
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Security: if you are into security, we need you! Although security\n"
"    advisories from the FreeBSD project are tracked and fixed, we can always\n"
"    use help in this area.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:811
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Contacts: we need people who can get in touch with FreeBSD developers to\n"
"    maintain contacts between us and the original project to exchange patches\n"
"    and discuss various problems and their solutions. Note that this should\n"
"    never involve any kind of spamming of mailing lists or IRC channels.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:817
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Testing: the more people are actively using Gentoo/FreeBSD, the more bugs\n"
"    will be discovered, which helps us improving the quality of the port. If\n"
"    you are good at describing bugs or problems, we definitely want to hear\n"
"    from you.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/gentoo-freebsd.xml:823
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Other areas where we need help include: system ebuilds, creation of\n"
